üéâMADISONIAN YEARBOOK GIVEAWAYüéâ

The Madisonian staff is giving away TWO FREE 2019-2020 yearbooks to FMHS students who do the following:
1) Follow us on Instagram @madisonianyearbook
2) Like our FMHS Madisonian Yearbook Facebook Page.
3) DM us on Instagram a picture with a caption of how you're spending your COVID-19 shutdown.
4) Submit at least one picture to the district's Facebook event called Bloodhound Spirit Weeks. Every additional submission allows you an extra entry into the drawing.

The winner will be selected June 3. Facebook has nothing to do with this contest.

post_text:
The Fort Madison Community School District takes the safety of staff and students as our number one priority.

Our staff have increased our cleaning routines including increased sanitation procedures at all of our district facilities and busses.

Please remember to maintain and increase good hygiene practices. This includes washing your hands with warm soap and water, covering sneezes and coughs with your elbow. Students should not come to school if they are feeling ill.

The FMCSD will continue to take direction from the Lee County Health Department (LCHD) and the Center for Disease Control (CDC.) At this time, there have been no recommendations for a change in school schedules. Below are two helpful links from the CDC and the Iowa Department of Public Health (IDPH).

https://www.cdc.gov/coronavirus/2019-ncov/index.html
https://idph.iowa.gov/Emerging-Health-Issues/Novel-Coronavirus

post_text:
A voted PPEL provides funds for major maintenance repairs in our FMCSD schools and it is now time to pursue a VPPEL to have funds for maintenance projects and repairs. Not passing the VPPEL means the district misses out on up to $10 million over the next ten years to invest in existing properties.
The vast majority of Iowa School districts who pursue a VPPEL do so successfully.

To find out more please visit: https://www.fmcsd.org/2020/02/14/voted-physical-plant-and-equipment-levy-vppel-faq/
text:
A voted PPEL provides funds for major maintenance repairs in our FMCSD schools and it is now time to pursue a VPPEL to have funds for maintenance projects and repairs. Not passing the VPPEL means the district misses out on up to $10 million over the next ten years to invest in existing properties.
The vast majority of Iowa School districts who pursue a VPPEL do so successfully.

To find out more please visit: https://www.fmcsd.org/2020/02/14/voted-physical-plant-and-equipment-levy-vppel-faq/

The Lee County Auditor's Office will have absentee voting in office through 5:00 pm on March 2, 2020.

If you are wanting to vote by mail please note that the auditor's office can no longer accept requests for mailed ballots after 5:00 pm on February 21, 2020. This is also the pre-registration deadline for this election.

request a ballot: http://bit.ly/2SYenpU
We appreciate a like and share to get the word out.

A voted PPEL provides funds for major maintenance repairs in our FMCSD schools. It is now time to pursue a VPPEL to have funds for maintenance projects.
Vote on March 3rd, 2020 or vote absentee.

If the VPPEL receives fewer than 50%+1 yes votes the district will lose out on $1million/year for up to ten years.

Here are the answers to the most frequently asked questions.
https://www.fmcsd.org/2020/02/14/voted-physical-plant-and-equipment-levy-vppel-faq/

The Fort Madison Community School District School Board voted unanimously to bring forth a Voted Physical Plant and Equipment Levy (PPEL) to the voters in the district. The date for this special election is March 3rd, 2020.

Fort Madison Community School District is a safe and nurturing community of students and staff that offers state of the art educational opportunities, and is a wonderful place to plant roots and raise a family! Keeping our schools modern and operational is vital for the growth and future of the community.

https://www.fmcsd.org/2020/01/08/board-votes-to-hold-special-election-in-march/
